# Implementation Plan: Deep Learning Indicator Optimization

## Goal

Look back through the entire historical OHLCV + indicator dataset for each symbol and **learn — via deep learning — what the optimal value of every indicator parameter would have been** to give the correct price direction signal at each point in time. Then persist those discovered optimal parameters and use them in live predictions.

Your machine (i9-14900KS · RTX 5090 31 GB · 192 GB RAM) makes this fully viable in minutes even for the full NIFTY 500 universe.

---

## Core Idea (Plain Language)

> **Current system**: Fixed indicator parameters (RSI=14, BB=20, ATR=14, etc.) → compute signals → vote → predict.
>
> **New system**: For every bar of historical data, a deep learning model looks at recent OHLCV patterns and **predicts the best parameter values for that moment** → compute signals with those parameters → predict. Then the model is trained so that those parameter choices maximised directional accuracy over all past dates.

This is achieved via **three complementary deep learning approaches**, all integrated into the existing `optimization/` package:

