## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1: PyTorch already installed?**
> Do you have PyTorch with CUDA already installed in your Python environment? (You can check: `python -c "import torch; print(torch.cuda.is_available())"`)
> If not, I'll include the correct install command for RTX 5090 (CUDA 12.x).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2: Training granularity**
> Should the DL model learn **one global model** across all NIFTY 50/500 symbols (recommended — more data, better generalization, uses the full GPU), or **one model per symbol** (more specific, slower)?
> **Recommended**: Global model first, then per-symbol fine-tuning.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q3: Sequence length / lookback**
> How many bars of history should the LSTM see when deciding the optimal parameters for today?
> - **60 bars** (~3 months of daily data) — default
> - **120 bars** (~6 months) — richer context but slower
> - **252 bars** (~1 year) — best for regime detection but needs more data per symbol

> [!NOTE]
> **Q4: What to do when DL model is not available at prediction time?**
> The system will automatically fall back: DL model → numgrad optimizer → default config (same existing precedence chain). No disruption to existing pipeline.

